HOW TO INSTALL THE THEME
************************

Open a terminal, go to where the compressed file is (with the command for example: "cd Downloads") and copy and paste this command:

with sudo:
----------
sudo tar -zxvf 136162-Crunchy-themes.tar.gz -C /usr/share

with su (if you don't have sudo):
---------------------------------
su
tar -zxvf 136162-Crunchy-themes.tar.gz -C /usr/share

In Gnome-shell, open 'gnome-tweak'
In Ubuntu, install and use 'unity-tweak'
Elsewhere, the Control Center Settings Manager is easy to use to change in the "appearance" (gtk theme) & the "window manager" (window decoration)

GNOME-SHELL NEW SETTINGS
========================
If you use either the "Gnome-Classic" session or the extension "Window-List", you can customize this extension.

2 files are already copied (with _Crunchy in the name inside the extension folder). It's because we can't theme it. So you have to save the original file and then, copy the "crunchy" ones instead :

in a terminal:
su
password
cd /usr/share/gnome-shell/extensions/window-list@gnome-shell-extensions.gcampax.github.com
cp classic.css classic_Origin.css
cp stylesheet.css stylesheet_Origin.css
cp classic_Crunchy.css classic.css
cp stylesheet_Crunchy.css stylesheet.css

HOW TO UNINSTALL THE THEME
**************************

Open a terminal and paste these command lines:

sudo rm -f -r /usr/share/fluxbox/styles/0*Crunchy*
sudo rm -f -r /usr/share/icewm/themes/0*Crunchy*
sudo rm -f -r /usr/share/themes/00-Customizations
sudo rm -f -r /usr/share/themes/0*Crunchy*
